Description:
Successful city attorney Nina Berkutova was sure of things in life --
a happy family, career development and peace of mind. In her
42 years, she seemed to have reached it all. But suddenly everything
changed dramatically. Her husband went to another woman, she
was deprived of her favorite work, the children moved away from her.
What is the inevitable cost of the illusory idea of success and
happiness? Nina has to rethink her life, to review relations with the
people closest to her. She now begins to regard her clients not only
as "customers." She tends to win court cases, not for the sake of
professional prestige, but from a desire to help people in distress.
She undertakes to protect the disadvantaged and needy: women who
have been abused and can not afford an expensive attorney, or poor
elderly people who suffer from bureaucratic arbitrariness.
"Who, if not I?", she he says to herself, beginning another, seemingly
hopeless cause!
